<inglise> ANNEX </inglise>
<eesti> LISA </eesti>
<inglise> ALTERNATIVE STAFF MEDICAL CHECK-UP SCHEME FOR PERSONS EMPLOYED TO WORK WITH OR HANDLE FRESH MEAT, POULTRYMEAT AND MEAT PRODUCTS PRESENTED BY THE AUTHORITIES OF DENMARK </inglise>
<eesti> TAANI AMETIASUTUSTE ESITATUD V&Auml;RSKE LIHAGA, KODULINNULIHAGA JA LIHATOODETEGA T&Ouml;&Ouml;ALASELT KOKKUPUUTUVATE ISIKUTE ALTERNATIIVSE ARSTLIKU L&Auml;BIVAATUSE KORD </eesti>
<inglise> A. Medical examination before taking up employment </inglise>
<eesti> A. Arstlik l&auml;bivaatus enne t&ouml;&ouml;leasumist </eesti>
<inglise> - The health of each person who is to be employed to handle meat, poultrymeat or meat products must be examined. </inglise>
<eesti> - K&otilde;ikide lihaga, kodulinnulihaga v&otilde;i lihatoodetega t&ouml;&ouml;alaselt kokkupuutuvate isikute tervist tuleb kontrollida. </eesti>
<inglise> The said examination is a pre-condition of such employment. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud tervisekontroll on k&otilde;nealuse t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise eeltingimus. </eesti>
<inglise> - The health check, on the basis of which the risk of contamination through the person concerned is assessed, must include an inquiry into the medical history carried out by means of a questionnaire (see under E), which must be assessed by a doctor, and a general medical examination carried out by a medical doctor. </inglise>
<eesti> - Tervisekontroll, mis on k&otilde;nealuse isiku nakkuseohu hindamise aluseks, koosneb haigusloo uurimisest k&uuml;simustiku abil (vt punkt E), mida hindab arst, ja arsti l&auml;biviidavast &uuml;ldisest tervisekontrollist. </eesti>
<inglise> Such medical examination may, if the doctor concerned considers it necessary, include a number of tests. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud tervisekontroll v&otilde;ib sisaldada mitmeid proove, kui asjaomane arst peab seda vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise> B. (Annual) routine examination </inglise>
<eesti> B. (Iga-aastane) korraline l&auml;bivaatus </eesti>
<inglise> - Whenever the medical authorities service concerned (attached to an undertaking) or the family doctor of the employee concerned considers it necessary in particular when suspicion exists in relation to the diseases listed in the questionnaires under E and F, but at least once a year, the health of the staff referred to in A must be assessed by means of a questionnaire (see under F). </inglise>
<eesti> - Punktis A osutatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervist hinnatakse k&uuml;simustiku abil (vt punkt F), eelk&otilde;ige seoses k&uuml;simustiku punktides E ja F loetletud haiguste kahtlusega, kui asutuse asjaomane meditsiiniteenistus v&otilde;i asjaomase t&ouml;&ouml;taja perearst peab seda vajalikuks, kuid v&auml;hemalt kord aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> - The questionnaire, when completed by the personnel, is to be submitted to the medical authorities concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> - T&ouml;&ouml;tajate poolt t&auml;idetud k&uuml;simustik esitatakse asjaomastele meditsiiniasutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> The doctor in charge has to sign this declaration, thus prolonging the medical certificate for one year. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastutav arst allkirjastab k&otilde;nealuse k&uuml;simustiku, millega arstit&otilde;endi kehtivus pikeneb &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> If the medical doctor, on basis of the questionnaire or on basis of any other information considers that there is a need for further medical assessment, a possible prolongation of the medical certificate can only be made after the results of such an assessment have been made available. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui arst leiab k&uuml;simustiku v&otilde;i muu teabe alusel, et on vaja l&auml;bi viia t&auml;iendav meditsiiniline uurimine, v&otilde;ib arstit&otilde;endit pikendada ainult p&auml;rast k&otilde;nealuse uurimise tulemuste selgumist. </eesti>
<inglise> Such an assessment may, if the doctor concerned considers it necessary, include a number of tests. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud uurimine v&otilde;ib sisaldada mitmeid proove, kui asjaomane arst peab seda vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise> - Where there is justification on epidemiological or clinical grounds, the medical service (attached to an undertaking) or the family doctor of the employee concerned ensures that persons who are a possible source of contamination are prohibited from working or handling fresh meat, poultrymeat or meat products. </inglise>
<eesti> - Kui epidemioloogilistel v&otilde;i kliinilistel p&otilde;hjustel on selleks alust, tagab meditsiiniteenistus (mis on seotud ettev&otilde;ttega) v&otilde;i asjaomase t&ouml;&ouml;taja perearst, et nakkuskahtlastel isikutel keelatakse t&ouml;&ouml;alaselt kokku puutuda v&auml;rske liha, linnuliha v&otilde;i lihatoodetega. </eesti>
<inglise> C. Guidance in matters of hygiene </inglise>
<eesti> C. H&uuml;gieenijuhised </eesti>
<inglise> Anyone working with or handling fresh meat, poultrymeat or meat products must have undergone appropriate training, particularly as regards his/her responsibility in matters of food and personal hygiene. </inglise>
<eesti> V&auml;rske liha, kodulinnuliha v&otilde;i lihatoodetega t&ouml;&ouml;alaselt kokkupuutuvad isikud peavad olema l&auml;binud n&otilde;uetekohase koolituse, eelk&otilde;ige seoses antud isiku vastutusega toiduh&uuml;gieeni ja isikliku h&uuml;gieeni osas. </eesti>
<inglise> D. Further comments </inglise>
<eesti> D. Muud m&auml;rkused </eesti>
<inglise> Although a health certificate drawn up before taking up employment offers no absolute guarantee that the person concerned will not be a source of contamination, it is important when first employed to draw the attention to essential public health aspects such as the responsibility in matters of hygiene generally and the obligation to report any contagious disease during the term of employment. </inglise>
<eesti> Kuigi enne t&ouml;&ouml;leasumist koostatud arstit&otilde;end ei anna t&auml;ielikku kindlust selle kohta, et asjaomane isik ei osutu nakkuseallikaks, on oluline juhtida t&ouml;&ouml;leasumisel t&auml;helepanu p&otilde;hilistele tervishoiu aspektidele, nagu vastutus seoses &uuml;ldise h&uuml;gieeniga ja kohustus teatada kogu teenistusajal esinevatest nakkuslikest haigustest. </eesti>
<inglise> In this context, it is essential that the person concerned is sufficiently well informed of his role as a transmitter of disease. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealusel juhul on oluline, et asjaomane isik on piisavalt informeeritud oma osast nakkusekandjana. </eesti>
<inglise> The routine medical examination (normally taking place every year) of staff engaged in handling meat, poultrymeat and meat products has been carried out for many years in a number of countries, with the aim of reducing the risk of pathogenic micro-organisms being transmitted to the consumer through the meat, poultrymeat or meat products by the person concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Liha, kodulinnuliha ja lihatoodetega t&ouml;&ouml;alaselt kokkupuutuvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate perioodilist tervisekontrolli (mis toimub &uuml;ldjuhul igal aastal) on tehtud paljudes riikides mitmete aastate jooksul eesm&auml;rgiga v&auml;hendada ohtu, et patogeensed mikroobid kanduksid tarbijale liha, kodulinnuliha v&otilde;i lihatoodete kaudu, millega asjaomane isik t&ouml;&ouml;alaselt kokku puutub. </eesti>
<inglise> At various international meetings the question has been raised of whether such routine examinations, particularly of faeces, must necessarily form part of the measures to protect the consumer against contagious diseases that may be transmitted via badly handled meat, poultry meat or meat products. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahvusvahelistel kohtumistel on t&otilde;stetud k&uuml;simus, kas nimetatud perioodilised tervisekontrollid, eelk&otilde;ige fekaalide osas, peavad olema osa meetmetest, mille eesm&auml;rk on kaitsta tarbijat nakkuslike haiguste eest, mis v&otilde;ivad levida liha, kodulinnuliha v&otilde;i lihatoodete mittekvaliteetse k&auml;itlemise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise> The value of the routine examination of faeces for pathogenic intestinal bacteria, in particular, has repeatedly been called into question. </inglise>
<eesti> Patogeensete soolebakterite avastamiseks tehtav fekaalide perioodilise kontrollimise v&auml;&auml;rtus on korduvalt kahtluse alla seatud. </eesti>
<inglise> It emerges from the study of the reports of the abovementioned meeting that routine examinations, particularly of faeces samples, do not in any significant way contribute towards preventing contagious diseases from being transmitted to the consumer via meat, poultry meat or meat products; in other words, the examination at regular intervals of faeces and urine of staff for Salmonella and Shigellae is no longe considered to be relevant. </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool nimetatud kohtumiste aruannete uurimisest selgub, et perioodilised tervisekontrollid, eelk&otilde;ige roojaproovide osas, ei aita olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral v&auml;ltida liha, kodulinnuliha v&otilde;i lihatoodete kaudu nakkuslike haiguste levimist tarbijale; teisis&otilde;nu, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate fekaalide ja uriini perioodilist kontrollimist Salmonella ja Shigellae suhtes ei peeta enam vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise> There should only be examination where it is justified on epidemiological or clinical grounds. </inglise>
<eesti> Proovid tuleks teha ainult siis, kui selleks on alust epidemioloogilistel v&otilde;i kliinilistel p&otilde;hjustel. </eesti>
